description.en:
Term tests on literature reading and analysis
A- analysis of the text is done according to the analysis plan, all questions are answered with maximum precision and reference to corresponding theoretical sources; the answer demonstrates a very high level of independent and creative thinking and contributes to well-known interpretations of the text.
B- Analysis follows the plan; all questions are answered correctly and demonstrate very good knowledge of theoretical aspects; the answers reveal the ability of critical thinking and creativity at a very good level; it shows the knowledge of literary critics' opinions of the text.
C- Analysis follows the analysis plan in general, all questions are answered with various degrees of precision and demonstrate good knowledge of theoretical aspects; the answers reveal partial readiness of the student to analyse a piece of literature critically; the analysis shows good level of independent thinking.
D- Analysis answers some research questions and shows the student's satisfactory knowledge of some theoretical sources to support the analysis; there are some references to other critics' opinions; the analysis demonstrates satisfactory level of independent thinking and creativity;
E- Analysis demonstrates student's knowledge of some basic principles of literary analysis and his/her ability to apply them while analysisng a piece of literature in a conventional way; the analysis demonstrates a poor level of independent thinking and creativity;

